stylometry: Our group project was on chipotle. WE decided to this project because one of our group members, Tom, works there. He said their main problem at chipotle was they can get people through the lines fast enough and customers are turning away becaues they dont want to wait in the long lines. So we did a littke research on waiting times and customers per hour, arrival time, etc. So in our first two models we wanted to show that having 4 people behind the counter at Chipotle was less wait time for customers than only having 3 people behind the counter. Once we showed that, then we went on to show that even thought customers would wait in line less with 4 people it would also cost Chipotle more money because they have one extra person working behind the counter compared to 3. SO really it would be up to Chiptole to either spend the extra money for that extra person and that will make Chipotle have more customers and more revenue, or keep the same number of 3 people behind the counter and not pay extra for that person. I learned that there alot of different decisions that companies need to consider when starting their business and to keep it running. These different types of models will help companies stay successful through the years and maintain profit, expenses, etc.
